# Vue 3 Composition API Patterns

- **Script setup**: Use `<script setup lang="ts">` for all Vue components. Do not use Options API.
- **TypeScript strict mode**: Enable strict mode in tsconfig; avoid `any` and prefer explicit types.
- **Functional components**: Prefer presentational components with props and emits. Keep components stateless where possible; use composables for shared logic.
- **Tailwind CSS**: Use Tailwind utility classes for styling. Avoid inline styles or scoped CSS unless Tailwind cannot express the design. Prefer Tailwind’s design tokens (spacing, colors, typography).
- **Animations**: Mandate Framer Motion (or its Vue equivalent) for animations. Do not use manual CSS transitions for complex choreography.
- **Canonical Reference**: Reference `src/components/canonical-example.vue` for the gold standard on props, exports, and component architecture.

## Example

```vue
<script setup lang="ts">
defineProps<{ label: string }>()
</script>

<template>
  <button class="rounded-lg bg-primary px-4 py-2 text-white">
    {{ label }}
  </button>
</template>
```
